de.mslab.ciphers.helpers

Interface DifferentialActiveComponentsCounter

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CipherHelper
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AES128Helper, AES192Helper, AES256Helper, ARIA128Helper, ARIA192Helper, ARIA256Helper, ARIAHelper, BKSQ144Helper, BKSQ192Helper, BKSQ96Helper, BKSQHelper, KhazadHelper, KLEIN64Helper, KLEIN80Helper, KLEIN96Helper, KLEINHelper, LBlockHelper, LEDHelper, MCryptonHelper, PRESENT128Helper, PRESENTHelper, PRINCECoreHelper, SerpentHelper, SQUAREHelper, ThreeFishHelper, WhirlpoolCipherHelper

    public interface DifferentialActiveComponentsCounter
    Count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers. The point of non-linear operations differs depending on the cipher and where non-linear operations occur in the round functions.
